Years licensed: Least to mostClear all View mapDefective and dangerous productsWhen you are injured by a poorly designed or poorly made product, or fall ill due to food poisoning or dangerous drugs, you may benefit from the services of a defective and dangerous products lawyer who understands how businesses and insurance companies manage product liability. Many drugs, including the arthritis drug Vioxx and diet aids containing Phenylpropanolamine, are considered dangerous products, as are some medical devices (heart defibrillators) and ordinary appliances (space heaters). Asbestos and tobacco are also considered inherently dangerous. A defective and dangerous products lawyer discovers how and why a product was defective, whether insurance policies will pay for your losses based on product liability laws, and what you can expect to recover in damages.Defective and dangerous products lawyers in cities near Los Angeles, CAGlendaleLa PuenteLakewoodLong BeachLos AngelesNorth HollywoodNorthridgePasadenaSanta ClaritaTorranceVan NuysWhittierSee all cities in California Nearby attorneys in related practice areasPersonal Injury Lawyers 90024Wrongful Death Attorneys 90024Class Action Attorneys 90024Litigation Lawyers 90024See all practice areas Los Angeles, CA attorneys by top languagesSpanishMandarinSet LocationCity and stateCancelSave







