Kevin  Mayer works as Chief Strategy Officer at The Walt Disney Company. Mr. Mayer serves as an Advisor of Theorem Capital, LLC. He served as an Executive Vice President of New Corporate Strategy, Business Development & Technology Group at Walt Disney Company since June 2005. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Playboy.com, Inc. since February 2000. He served as the Chief Executive Officer, Senior Vice President and Chairman of Clear Channel Interactive. He was employed at L.E.K. Consulting LLC, where he served as a Partner and served as Head of the Global Media and Entertainment Practice.  Mr. Mayer served as an Executive Vice President and General Manager of the GO Network. He served as an Executive Vice President of Television Network Product and International at the Buena Vista Internet Group.  Mr. Mayer served in strategic planning at The Walt Disney Company, served as the Senior Vice President. He served as Executive Vice President of the Walt Disney Internet Group in 1990.  He served as a Management Consultant of The LEK Partnership. He serves as a Director of Hulu Japan LLC. He served as a Director of Playboy.com, Inc. since February 2000. He served as a Director of UTV Software Communications Limited.



